description: Launches the specified Scheduled Instances. Before you can launch a Scheduled Instance, you must purchase it and obtain an identifier using PurchaseScheduledInstances. You must launch a Scheduled Instance during its scheduled time period. You can't stop or reboot a Scheduled Instance, but you can terminate it as needed. If you terminate a Scheduled Instance before the current scheduled time period ends, you can launch it again after a few minutes. For more information, see Scheduled Instances in the Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud User Guide.
